"a.仰卧的；懒散的 【英】 adj. 仰卧的(lying on the back)；懒散的(mentally or morally slack) 【考】 反义词：vigilant(警 觉的) 【记】 sup(=super 在…上面)+ine→(肚 子)在上面→仰卧的； 【同】 参考：prone(俯卧的) adj. 仰卧的; 懒散的(消极的或漠不关心的) 【记】su酥, pine(n 松树; v 消瘦): 浑身消瘦酥麻是因为懒散 【反】vigilant(adj 警惕的) 【记】super + 音：拍，晚饭后拍拍肚子懒散地躺床上→仰卧 【相关】prone 俯卧 supine (adj.)  c.1500, ""lying on the back,"" from Latin supinus ""bent backwards, thrown backwards, lying on the back,"" figuratively ""inactive, indolent,"" from PIE *(s)up- (see sub-). The grammatical use for ""Latin verbal noun formed from the past participle stem"" (mid-15c.) is from Late Latin supinum verbum ""supine verb,"" perhaps so called because, though furnished with a noun case ending, it ""falls back"" on the verb. Related: Supinely."
